parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose vital information about the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and other essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: and other gauges on the instrument panel fail to function or display erratic readings
the instrument panel screen goes blank
the gauges spike or fluctuate randomly before failing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system shorts out
the instrument panel fails to function
the windows fail to open or close
the headlights or turn signals fail to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The headlights or low beam lights fail to function
the headlights turn off and on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights turn off or flicker while driving
sometimes returning to normal operation after a short time; the low beam headlights may not work
but the high beam headlights do; the headlights may work intermittently or only when the high beam switch is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause other drivers to not be aware of the vehicle's intentions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate or flicker when the brake pedal is pressed; the brake lights may not work
but other lights on the vehicle do.
